{"title": "Chastity Dagger", "content": "\"Unappalled by the calm dignity of blameless womanhood, your minion has torn me from my spotless home, and dragged me, blindfold and shrieking, through hedges, over stiles, and across a very difficult country, and left me, helpless and trembling, at your mercy! Yet not helpless, coward sir, for approach one step \u2014 nay, but the twentieth part of one poor inch \u2014 and this poniard shall teach ye what it is to lay unholy hands on old Stephen Trusty's daughter!\"\n\nThe villain has cornered a beautiful maiden! Trembling at the very thought of his touch, she tearfully lifts her skirt, things look bad \u2014 but what's this? She's pulled a knife from her garter! Before he can react, she stabs him, saving her virtue and possibly putting an end to his evil ways once and for all.\n\nThe Chastity Dagger is the favored weapon of delicate, civilized young ladies in fantasy and historical works. It is almost always used as a means of self-defense when in danger of being raped, robbed or kidnapped, but a Femme Fatale may also use it in conjunction with her feminine charm to assassinate a male character while he is distracted. A more modern variation is the Little Useless Gun.\n\nAn inversion almost as common as the trope itself is when the knife is like a Cyanide Pill for suicide rather than self-defensive \u2014 averting Fate Worse than Death and invoking Better to Die than Be Killed.\n\nSubtrope of Hidden Weapons; Trouser Space is favourite, but Victoria's Secret Compartment is another option. See also Silk Hiding Steel.\n\nFor a fantastic, Body Horror variation, see Vagina Dentata. Though it should be noted that that trope is almost never used in applying this trope, unless it's part of a Karmic Death or Mugging the Monster situation meant to introduce the real Monster of the Week.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChastityDagger", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Ruddigore", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SamuraiChamploo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheEmperorsNewGroove", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RobinHoodPrinceOfThieves", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RobinHood2010", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RomancingTheStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SherlockHolmes2009", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheThreeMusketeers1993", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Troy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PansLabyrinth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TenThousandBC", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CircusOfHorrors", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ABrothersPrice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/ConanTheBarbarian", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Gor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SienkiewiczTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SwordOfTruth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThaisOfAthens", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/VorkosiganSaga", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Belgariad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheElenium", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TalesOfTheOtori", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheHunchbackOfNotreDame", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePillarsOfTheEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AladdinAndTheMagicLamp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePyrates", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/GameOfThrones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarTrek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Angel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Ruddigore", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/KingsQuestVI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MedievalIITotalWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Touhou", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Vampyr2018"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYouNowMyPretty", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProperLady", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FemmeFatale", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleUselessGun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CyanidePill", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FateWorseThanDeath", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetterToDieThanBeKilled", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HiddenWeapons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrouserSpace", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Victor